  "texts": [
    "Although there seems to be no clear best prompting strategies across models or tasks, performance improvements clearly could be made by choosing the optimal prompting strategy.",
    "For instance, the accuracy for Zephyr-7B-Beta on PubMedQA dataset was enhanced from 18.40% to 59.40% by changing from a short, zero-shot prompt to a long, few-shot prompt with random examples.",
    "Figure 2 summarizes the average best performance of each model by task.",
    "We consider each model, prompt, and dataset as one combination and report the average per-model score across datasets of the same task.",
    "Overall, GPT-4 showed the highest average best performance for all tasks, followed by Flan-T5-XXL and GPT-3.5-turbo, then Zephyr-7B-Beta and MedLLaMA-13B."
  ],
